  <h1>
   draw_point
  </h1>
  With this function you can draw a single pixel anywhere on the screen, using the currently set draw colour and alpha.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_point(x, y);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      x
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The x coordinate of the point to be drawn.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      y
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The y coordinate of the point to be drawn.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_set_colour(c_yellow); draw_point(100,100);
</code></pre>
  This will draw a yellow pixel at position (100,100).
 </body>
